sentiment_score_definition: x <= -0.35: Bearish; -0.35 < x <= -0.15: Somewhat-Bearish; -0.15 < x < 0.15: Neutral; 0.15 <= x < 0.35: Somewhat_Bullish; x >= 0.35: Bullish

feed.title: OCONNOR A Distinct Business Unit of UBS ASSET MANAGEMENT AMERICAS LLC Invests $1.03 Million in Jackson Acquisition Company II $JACS
feed.summary: OCONNOR, a unit of UBS Asset Management Americas, recently acquired a new stake of 100,000 shares in Jackson Acquisition Company II (NYSE:JACS), valued at approximately $1.03 million. Other institutional investors like Goldman Sachs and Wolverine Asset Management also made significant moves in JACS stock. Despite this institutional interest, Weiss Ratings maintains a "sell (d-)" rating for the company, and its shares are trading near $10.44 after reporting $0.08 EPS for the last quarter.

feed.title: Wolverine Asset Management LLC Increases Stock Holdings in Jackson Acquisition Company II $JACS
feed.summary: Wolverine Asset Management LLC significantly increased its stake in Jackson Acquisition Company II (NYSE:JACS) by 85.1% in the second quarter, now holding 626,322 shares valued at $6.45 million. Goldman Sachs Group Inc. also acquired a new stake, indicating growing institutional interest. Despite this, the stock carries a consensus "Sell" rating from analysts like Weiss Ratings.

feed.title: Private companies own 18% of Jackson Acquisition Company II (NYSE:JACS) shares but individual investors control 60% of the company
